    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="faq-section section-pad" id="faq">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="text-center mb-5" data-aos="fade-up">
                <span class="eyebrow">Frequently Asked</span>
                <h2 class="section-title">Zoho in the <span class="text-grad">UAE — FAQ</span></h2>
                <p class="section-sub">Answers to common questions about deploying Zoho for UAE businesses.</p>
            </div>

            <div class="row justify-content-center">
                <div class="col-lg-9">
                    <div class="faq-item open" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Is Zoho suitable for UAE companies (LLC, FZ, Mainland)?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Yes. Zoho works well for Mainland LLCs, Free Zone companies (DMCC, JAFZA, DIFC, ADGM, RAKEZ, IFZA, etc.), Sole Establishments and Branches. We configure VAT, currencies (AED + multi-currency), languages (Arabic / English RTL), payroll components (WPS, EOSB, GPSSA) and integrations needed for UAE operations.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Does Zoho Books support UAE VAT and FTA e-invoicing?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Zoho Books has a UAE-specific edition with built-in 5% VAT, VAT201 returns, reverse charge handling, designated zone treatment, and e-invoicing-ready document workflows aligned with the FTA's upcoming mandate.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Can Zoho Payroll handle WPS, EOSB and GPSSA?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Yes. Zoho Payroll UAE generates MOHRE WPS SIF files for salary disbursement, calculates EOSB (gratuity) per UAE Labour Law, and handles GPSSA contributions for UAE/GCC nationals — with Arabic/English payslips delivered through Zoho People self-service.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">What about UAE payment gateways and BNPL?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Zoho integrates with Telr, Network International (N-Genius), PayTabs, Checkout.com, Stripe MENA, and BNPL providers Tabby and Tamara through APIs / Zoho Flow — enabling cards, Apple Pay, and split payments on invoices and Zoho Commerce checkouts.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Can we migrate from Tally / QuickBooks / Sage / SAP B1 / Salesforce?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Yes. We migrate customers, vendors, items, opening balances, transactions and HR data from Tally, QuickBooks, Sage 50/200, Odoo, SAP B1, Salesforce, HubSpot and Excel — with mapping, validation and reconciliation built into the cutover plan.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Is Zoho compliant with UAE PDPL and Corporate Tax?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Zoho supports role-based access, field-level security, encryption, MFA, audit logs and DPA controls — aligned with Federal Decree-Law No. 45 of 2021 (PDPL). For Corporate Tax (9% from June 2023), we configure GL, tax-period reporting, and the necessary financial statements in Zoho Books.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">Does Zoho work with WhatsApp Business and UAE marketplaces (Noon, Amazon.ae)?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Yes. Zoho CRM and Desk have native WhatsApp Business integration. We connect Noon, Amazon.ae, Namshi and Carrefour Online using Zoho Flow, partner connectors or APIs to sync orders, inventory and customers.</p></div></div>
                    <div class="faq-item" data-aos="fade-up"><button class="q">How long does an implementation take and what does it cost?<i class="fa-solid fa-plus"></i></button><div class="a"><p>Typical Zoho CRM rollout: 3–6 weeks. Books + Payroll: 4–8 weeks. Zoho One multi-app rollout: 8–16 weeks. Pricing depends on scope, users and integrations — we provide a fixed-fee quote in AED after a free discovery call.</p></div></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

